T1	Intervention 687 928	assigned to receive either fentanyl (10 micrograms/mL) or a fentanyl/bupivacaine (0.1%) mixture epidurally corresponding to the dermatome of the surgical incision in a double-blind fashion for the first 18 hours after major abdominal surgery
T2	Intervention 930 1223	The infusion was titrated for each patient to the rate required for pain relief during forced inspiration (pain score < or = 2, maximum 10). Pain scores, the fentanyl doses required, plasma concentrations of fentanyl at 18 hours, and the incidence and severity of adverse effects were recorded
